<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.1//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml11/DTD/xhtml11.dtd">
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
	<head>
		<title>CSS Test: opacity</title>
  <style type="text/css">
    @page { font: italic 8pt sans-serif; color: gray;
            margin: 7%;
            counter-increment: page;
            @top-left { content: "CSS Color Module Level 3 Conformance Test Suite"; }
            @top-right { content: "Test t32-opacity-offscreen-with-alpha-c"; }
            @bottom-right { content: counter(page); }
          }
</style>
		<link rel="author" title="L. David Baron" href="http://dbaron.org/"/>
		<link rel="author" title="Mozilla Corporation" href="http://mozilla.com/"/>
		<link rel="help" href="http://www.w3.org/TR/css3-color/#transparency"/>
		<meta name="flags" content=""/>
		<meta name="assert" content="That alpha within the offscreen buffer is composited correctly."/>
		<style type="text/css"><![CDATA[

		body { background: white; }

		div { width: 5em; height: 1em; }
		div.top { margin: 2px 0; }

		]]></style>
	</head>
	<body>
		<p>The following four boxes should be the same color:</p>

		<div class="top" style="background: rgb(204, 204, 255)"/>
		<div class="top" style="opacity: 0.2; background: rgb(0, 0, 255)"/>
		<div class="top" style="opacity: 0.5"><div style="opacity: 0.4; background: rgb(0, 0, 255)"/></div>
		<div class="top" style="opacity: 0.4"><div style="background: rgba(0, 0, 255, 0.5)"/></div>
	</body>
</html>